         Division Summary
         @WalmartLabs is the technical powerhouse behind Walmart Global eCommerce. We employ big data at scale -- from machine learning, data mining and optimization algorithms, to modeling and analyzing massive flows of data from online, social, mobile and offline commerce. We don’t just engineer cool websites, mobile apps, and new services; we use our own open source tools to create the framework. Deployment is automated and accelerated through our open cloud platform. This makes us incredibly nimble and able to adjust in real-time to our global customers.
         Department Summary
         Looking for a college internship loaded with learning opportunities and career building acumen, all in a fun, collaborative environment?  As a Walmart Global eCommerce intern or new grad, you’ll work on real projects you can really sink your teeth into.  You’ll collaborate with some of the most talented technologists in the digital space.  Your experience is sweetened through participation in our executive speaker series, tech talks, lunch and learns, community service and social events, which will give you a broader understanding of the world’s largest retailer and the industry.  Sure beats coffee runs.
         Position Summary
         The CRM data science team @WalmartLabs is a cross-functional team of scientists and engineers. It aims developing data-driven models, tools and applications to understand and improve customer's engagement. The intern project focuses on developing a real-time customer life time value prediction modeling system by mining customer engagement data (purchase, browsing, search, email response, app usage, etc.).  Major tasks include data processing, feature engineering and model testing.
